# File Structure

Use these folders for new code:

- `src/app`: app assembly, route contracts, navigation, global config.
- `src/pages/<page>`: route-level page contracts and future page implementations.
- `src/widgets/<widget>/ui`: large composed page regions.
- `src/features/<feature>/ui`: user-facing workflows and interactions.
- `src/entities/<entity>/model`: stable domain types and entity contracts.
- `src/shared/ui`: reusable UI helpers and small primitives.
- `src/shared/contracts`: reusable cross-domain types.
- `src/styles`: global styles, tokens, HeroUI imports, and responsive rules.

Naming:

- React component files use `PascalCase.tsx`.
- Non-component modules use `kebab-case.ts`.
- Type-only domain files use `types.ts`.
- Page metadata files use `contract.ts`.
- Test files live next to the unit under test as `*.test.tsx` or `*.test.ts`.

Do not create generic folders like `components`, `utils`, or `helpers` unless the existing layer cannot express the ownership clearly.
